# Lesson 3 – Manager Tools: The Trinity & Effective 1on1s

**Course:** Leadership & Management Class Program (1 hour / week)  
**Date:** TBD  
**Duration:** 60 minutes  
**Prerequisite lesson:** Lesson 2 – Manager Tools: Power Triangle & The Trinity

## Learning Objectives

By the end of this session, participants will be able to:

- Explain why 1on1s are the foundation of the Manager Tools Trinity and how they build relationship power and trust.
- Describe the difference between “good” and “bad” 1on1 experiences from the direct’s point of view.
- Answer the core design questions for 1on1s: why we do them, cadence, length, ownership, and agenda.
- Explain why sporadic or frequently-moved 1on1s erode safety and credibility.
- Outline a simple 1on1 structure (preparation, execution, aftermath) and connect it to active listening and future feedback.

